---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const jsonLD = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'WebPage', name: 'Privacy Policy' };
const updated = '2026-07-17';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="How VisaLang handles visitor data, URL state, local storage, and server logs." jsonLD={jsonLD} noindex={true}>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <article class="guide-article narrow-page">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="guide-summary">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>VisaLang (visalang.org) is a static informational website. We do not require you to create an account, and we do not collect sensitive personal data such as passport numbers, immigration documents, or payment details.</p>

        <h2>Services and information we use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> VisaLang does not currently load Google AdSense or another advertising network. No advertising consent mechanism is currently active. Advertising will remain disabled until its consent, privacy, security-header, and regional requirements have been reviewed and tested.</li>
          <li><strong>Tool and route progress:</strong> after a tool successfully generates a result, it places only the non-sensitive values needed to restore that result in the page URL. Use the tool’s restart control to remove those URL values. Route pages separately store the current route step in your browser’s local storage; clear site data to remove that route-step progress.</li>
          <li><strong>Direct contact:</strong> if you email us, your email provider and ours process the address, message, and any information you choose to include.</li>
          <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> standard web server logs (IP address, user agent, timestamp) retained for security and debugging purposes.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Please do not send sensitive case documents</h2>
        <p>Do not send passport scans, visa files, certificate copies, booking codes, or payment records through a public contact channel. VisaLang does not need them to assess a correction and cannot verify an individual application or certificate.</p>

        <h2>How we use information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To respond to corrections, questions, product-update requests, or partnership inquiries that you send directly.</li>
          <li>To maintain site security and prevent abuse.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies and privacy choices</h2>
        <p>VisaLang does not currently load an advertising consent message because display advertising is paused. You can clear URL values with a tool’s restart control and remove route-step progress by clearing site data in your browser.</p>

        <h2>Third-party links</h2>
        <p>Our guides link to official exam providers and government authorities. Once you leave visalang.org, their privacy policies apply. We are not responsible for practices on external sites.</p>

        <h2>Advertising</h2>
        <p>Display advertising is currently disabled. VisaLang will update this policy before enabling an advertising network, consent platform, or related third-party storage.</p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>If you contacted us and want your message or email address removed where applicable, contact <a href="/contact/">us</a>. Residents of the EU, UK, and California may have additional rights under GDPR or CCPA.</p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>VisaLang is not directed at children under 16 and we do not knowingly collect their data.</p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>We may update this policy when our services, consent choices, or data practices change. The Last Updated date above reflects the most recent revision.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about privacy? See our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>

        <p class="compliance-line">This privacy policy is provided for informational purposes and does not constitute legal advice.</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
